<Content>Location and charm but... I've stayed at this hotel several times. I just love the old Boston feel. The lobby is fabulous and being in that part of town is great. I stay there when I to go Newbury Street and the Theatre District. It close to many things I enjoy and it's a not a new stark hotel with white walls. It has character and class, period. Unfortunately, they can not seem to get their reservation department together. The first contact with customers in not good.... I've called and spoken with managers about it but it still has not changed. It is a real hassle to get a reservation, not just once or twice either.... Do not join their email list, it's NOT helpful at all for speicals. They offer specials for shopping, spa experience etc, which is great. The really just include valet parketing in the price, which is pretty good seeing it's about $50 to park so be prepared to pay. The concierge level is pretty good. I feel secure there. Also, at night, you must show your room key in order to get on the elevator. When you walk off the elevator onto the concierge level their is almost always a friendly face to greet you. The lougne on that floor is small but nice. The people are not overly friendly but fine. The morning buffet is small but adequate. The nice nuts and bottled water in your room is a treat. The rooms are generally small but quaint. Some would consider the rooms too hot but I like it that way. The lobby lounges are great. You feel comfortable and they're charming and ageless but a bit over priced. The free appetizers are good but they run out fast There is a night club on the property at the ground level and they try to manage it but sometimes it's loud. I've had dinner in there and it's okay but there are so many other great places to eat. They do have a small workout area but I'm genearlly only there a short time and usually, I'm too busy to visit it. I wish the service was better but the location and security is excellent. 
